---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Molten" description="Molten's privacy policy - your data stays private and secure">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="gradient-orange text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <div class="text-5xl mb-6">ðŸ”’</div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/90">
        Last updated: November 26, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Content -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Our Commitment to Your Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          At Molten, we believe your creative work and inventory data should remain completely private.
          We've designed the app from the ground up with privacy as a core principle, not an afterthought.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          <strong>Simple summary:</strong> Your inventory data stays on your devices and in your iCloud account.
          We only collect minimal technical data to fix bugs and improve the app.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What We Don't Collect -->
      <div class="mb-12 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">What We DON'T Collect</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't collect your inventory data</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't access your personal notes or tags</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't track your in-app behavior or usage patterns</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't sell or share your data with third parties for advertising</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't use advertising networks</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600">âœ—</span>
            <span>We don't require account creation or login</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Data Storage -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Where Your Data Lives</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Local Storage</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
              All your inventory data is stored locally on your device using
              Apple's Core Data framework. This data never leaves your device unless you enable iCloud sync.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">iCloud Sync (Optional)</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-3">
              If you enable iCloud sync, your inventory data is synchronized between your devices using Apple's CloudKit
              framework. This means:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
              <li>Your data syncs directly between your devices via your personal iCloud account</li>
              <li>We never have access to your synced data</li>
              <li>Apple encrypts your data in transit and at rest</li>
              <li>Only you can access this data through your Apple ID</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-3">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Catalog data (the 2,500+ glass items in our database) is stored locally and does not sync via iCloud to prevent unnecessary data duplication.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Photos</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
              Custom photos you add for glass items are stored in your device's local storage
              and backed up via iCloud if you have iCloud backup enabled. These photos are never
              sent to our servers.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Cloud Backups (Pro Feature)</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-3">
              Pro subscribers can enable automatic cloud backups of their inventory data to our servers. These backups are:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
              <li>Indexed by a randomly-generated ID created on your device â€” we cannot link backups to you personally</li>
              <li>Stored on Cloudflare's infrastructure</li>
              <li>Completely under your control â€” you can disable backups or delete all backup data at any time from the app</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Inventory Sharing (Optional)</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-3">
              You can choose to share your inventory with others by generating a sharing code. When you share:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
              <li>You control what display name is shown to people you share with</li>
              <li>Only people you give your sharing code to can view your inventory</li>
              <li>You can revoke access at any time by turning off sharing</li>
              <li>Shared data is automatically deleted after 90 days of inactivity</li>
              <li>Shared inventory data is stored on Cloudflare's infrastructure while sharing is active</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What We Do Collect -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Information We Collect</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Crash Reports and Error Logs</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-3">
              We use <a href="https://sentry.io" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sentry</a>,
              a third-party error tracking service, to collect crash reports and error logs. This helps us identify and fix bugs quickly.
              The data collected includes:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
              <li>Device type and iOS version</li>
              <li>App version and build number</li>
              <li>Error type and stack trace (technical debugging information)</li>
              <li>General operation context (e.g., "catalog download failed")</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-3">
              This data does <strong>not</strong> include your inventory, projects, personal notes, or any identifying information.
              Sentry's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sentry.io/privacy</a>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Bug Reports (User-Initiated)</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-3">
              If you shake your device to submit a bug report, you can optionally include:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
              <li>A description of the issue you encountered</li>
              <li>Your email address (if you want a response)</li>
              <li>Device information (app version, device model, iOS version)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-3">
              All fields are optional, and the report is only sent when you choose to submit it.
              Bug reports are sent to Sentry for tracking and resolution.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">App Store Analytics</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
              When you download Molten from the App Store, Apple may share basic analytics with us such as
              number of downloads, app usage statistics, and crash reports. This data is anonymized by Apple
              and cannot be linked to individual users. You can control this in your device's Privacy settings
              under "Analytics & Improvements."
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Support Communications</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
              If you contact us via email for support, we retain your email and the content of your message
              to help resolve your issue. We never share this information with third parties.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Your Rights -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Your Rights and Controls</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          You have complete control over your data:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Delete your data:</strong> Uninstalling the app removes all local data. iCloud data can be managed in your iCloud settings.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Delete cloud backups:</strong> Delete all your cloud backup data at any time from the app's Settings.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Stop sharing:</strong> Revoke inventory sharing access instantly by turning off sharing in the app.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Disable iCloud sync:</strong> Turn off iCloud sync in your device's Settings to keep data local only.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Control Apple analytics:</strong> Adjust Settings â†’ Privacy & Security â†’ Analytics & Improvements on your device.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">âœ“</span>
            <span><strong>Request data deletion:</strong> Contact us at info@moltenglass.app to request deletion of any data we hold (support emails, bug reports).</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Third-Party Services -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Molten uses the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li>
            <strong>Apple CloudKit:</strong> For optional iCloud sync of your user data.
            <br/>
            <span class="text-gray-600">Privacy: <a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">apple.com/privacy</a></span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple App Store:</strong> For app distribution and optional analytics.
            <br/>
            <span class="text-gray-600">Privacy: <a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">apple.com/privacy</a></span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sentry:</strong> For crash reporting and error tracking.
            <br/>
            <span class="text-gray-600">Privacy: <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sentry.io/privacy</a></span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare:</strong> For hosting our website, cloud backups, and inventory sharing.
            <br/>
            <span class="text-gray-600">Privacy: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a></span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Data Retention -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Data Retention</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>Local app data:</strong> Retained until you delete the app or clear its data.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>iCloud data:</strong> Retained in your iCloud account until you delete it.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>Cloud backups:</strong> Retained until you delete them from the app or disable backups.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>Shared inventory data:</strong> Automatically deleted after 90 days of inactivity, or immediately when you turn off sharing.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>Error logs:</strong> Sentry retains error data for 90 days by default.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-500">â€¢</span>
            <span><strong>Support emails:</strong> Retained as long as needed to resolve your issue, then archived.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Children's Privacy -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          Molten is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
          The minimal data we collect (error logs) does not include information that identifies individual users.
          If you believe a child has submitted personal information to us, please contact us at info@moltenglass.app.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- International Users -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">International Users</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          Molten is operated from the United States. If you are using the app from outside the United States,
          please be aware that any information you provide (such as bug reports) may be transferred to and processed in the United States
          or other countries where our service providers operate. By using the app and submitting bug reports,
          you consent to this transfer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Changes to Privacy Policy -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700 ml-4">
          <li>Posting the new policy on this page</li>
          <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date at the top</li>
          <li>Notifying you via the app if the changes are significant</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-4">
          We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any changes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, want to request data deletion, or have concerns about how we handle your data, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg">
          <a href="mailto:info@moltenglass.app" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-600 font-bold">
            info@moltenglass.app
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 gradient-orange text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Your Privacy Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-8 text-white/90">
        Download Molten and experience inventory management designed with your privacy in mind.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/molten"
           class="bg-white text-orange-500 px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition">
          Download on App Store
        </a>
        <a href="/features"
           class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-white/20 transition border-2 border-white/30">
          Explore Features
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
